# README

zime: Zime Input Method Engine, an input method library designed for the Chinese language family

features:
- interchangeable schemas with a ubiquitous algorithm base
- major functionalities from modern input method stereotypes
- introduction of avant-guarde (sometimes PQliar) design
- tweakability++
- open-source 
- cross-platform

The zime alphabet: |
    zed wy ex,
    double-u vee u,
    tee ess ar,
    cue pee o,
    en em el kay jay i aitch,
    gee ef e dee cee bee a.

Sub-projects :

- ibus-rhyme : Linux/ibus client
- weasel     : Windows client
- squirrel   : planned Mac OS X client
- digit      : planned Android client; reimplementation of core algo in Java

- breeze     : schema repository
- essay      : the vocabulary
- grammar    : a language model
- plume      : planned web services

- combopinyin: innovative chord-typing practice

- zhung      : an romanization scheme in Zhungyuan phonology

Epilogue: |

    Sorry for the temporary short of documentation. Feel free to explore.

    Visit zime project home page http://zime.googlecode.com/ for lastest news.
    Questions go to <chen.sst@gmail.com>.

